                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/behat/edit/behat3/knpu/javascript-waiting.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Let's talk JavaScript and the complications it can cause. Right now everything runs
using the Goutte driver and background cURL requests. This means that if your behavior
relies on JavaScript, it'll fail. We need to use Selenium - or Zombie.js - another
supported JavaScript driver - for these scenarios.</p>
<p>I want this "New Product" button to <em>not</em> load a whole new page, but instead open up
a modal. I cheated and already did most of the work for this. Inside of <code>list.html.twig</code>,
add the class <code>js-add-new-product</code> to the "New Product" link:</p>
